{"title": "All Monks Know Kung-Fu", "content": "The main features of Christian monastic life are prayers (frequently chanted) and scholarship (reading, writing, healing etc.), sometimes corporeal penance for some Orthodox monks (e.g. flagellants, heavy fasting, etc.).\n\nThe main features of Buddhist monks from Shaolin are chanting, meditation and kick-ass martial arts prowess (which they originally learned from retired soldiers who became monks).\n\nFor some reason, fiction authors sometimes can't see the difference.\n\nIt's not uncommon (usually in fantasy settings) to see a Christian or quasi-Christian monk (often complete with robe, hood, tonsure, Christian name, etc.) whose main defining skills are one or all of the following:\n\u2022 having (and building, strengthening etc.) a very tough body\n\nIt seems that you're supposed to be able to do Shaolin-style things just because you're... well, a \"monk\".\n\nMake sure not to confuse this trope with examples of Shaolin-based monks who know kung fu, which is perfectly justified, since these particular monks learned from former soldiers, and practiced combat in secret or disguised as religious rituals (since it was generally illegal). But, if these Shaolin-based monks are supposed to belong to a Crystal Dragon Jesus religion, then these examples may belong here. Examples where every Chinese monk knows kung fu also belongs here, seeing as how most Chinese monastic orders do not engage in any martial arts training.\n\nThis trope is the sister (brother?) trope of Nuns Are Mikos. Compare to Everybody Was Kung-Fu Fighting, when everybody seems to know kung fu. (Most Chinese didn't). See also Enlightenment Superpowers for a result of all that meditating. Also compare to Not That Kind of Doctor (\"all guys called 'doctor something' know medicine\"), Open Heart Dentistry (\"all medical doctors know every medical discipline\") and Omnidisciplinary Scientist (\"all scientists know every science\"). Thematically related to Church Militant, Religious Bruiser, Warrior Monk (duh) and Bare-Fisted Monk (duh). ... And sometimes the One knowing kung fu isn't just a mere monk, but our Lord and Saviour Himself...", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllMonksKnowKungFu", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/LaskoDieFaustGottes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Braindead", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AliveTheFinalEvolution", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FirstSquad", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BattlePope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/FatherTed", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AAPessimal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JamesClavell", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BruceLee", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BrainDead", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Myth/RobinHood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ArmorOfGod", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheCrimsonRivers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheGamersDorknessRising", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FatalDeviation", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JohnnyMnemonic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DolphLundgren", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Neuromancer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/BrotherCadfael", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EllisPeters", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Myth/RobinHood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Redwall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/NealStephenson", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Anathem", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DavidCarradine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KungFu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/LaskoDieFaustGottes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Myth/RobinHood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/DungeonsAndDragons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Exalted", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HeroesOfMightAndMagic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MightAndMagic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DungeonKeeper", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DynastyWarriors", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/RagnarokOnline", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/NeverwinterNights2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheElderScrolls", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsVSkyrim", "/pmwiki/pmwik